Quite literally living my dreams.
When I look back on these photos, I get emotional. Sharing my life has came easy. Back when I got my first laptop I would spend hours recording and editing (cringe) videos of me and my friends. Back then, even though social media was new, I felt like it lacked representation. Representation in life struggles, in realness, in vulnerability. I struggled with my self perception for a long time. I hated that I was taller than 99% of my grade, I hated that I had horrible acne, I hated looking up to people that had unachievable lifestyles. 
This day right here was an absolute dream. I will never take this for granted. I’m so thankful to have this community - because while some of y’all have shared that I’ve helped you, I want you to know, y’all have done the same for me 🖤
